	<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-1916">
	<article id="article-comment-1916">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Andi</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">March 07, 2022 at 4:42 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>How large is your scoop for the protewin powder? Some of my protwein powders use a smaller scoop - 2 scoops for a 30g serving and some use a single scoop.</p>
<p>Thanks!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1916' data-commentid="1916" data-postid="2543" data-belowelement="article-comment-1916" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Andi" aria-label='Reply to Andi'>Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-jhgrave77 bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-1917">
	<article id="article-comment-1917">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Jessica</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">March 07, 2022 at 5:38 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Hey Andi, I used 1 scoop (25g) of protein powder. If your scoops weigh more than 25g, you could try adding an additional 1 tablespoon of milk to the batter. Let me know if you have any more questions!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-1917' data-commentid="1917" data-postid="2543" data-belowelement="article-comment-1917" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jessica" aria-label='Reply to Jessica'>Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

